Text.LocalizedString: If you see <NPCName>Kenny</>, would you tell him to come find me?//<portrait=concerned>He forgot to feed one of the cows.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind him playing his flute, but he should get his work done first.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind him playing his flute, but he should get his work done first.

Text.SourceString: Are your animals doing okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//We’ve got everything you need for them down at the ranch.
Text.LocalizedString: Are your animals doing okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//We’ve got everything you need for them down at the ranch.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kenny</> does all the work of caring for the animals, so there’s not much to do around here but sell supplies.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kenny</> does all the work of caring for the animals, so there’s not much to do around here but sell supplies.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind, though.//<portrait=normal>It gives me more time to maintain the shop’s inventory. Someone’s gotta do it, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind, though.//<portrait=normal>It gives me more time to maintain the shop’s inventory. Someone’s gotta do it, right?

Text.SourceString: You should never be rude to your animals.//They may not understand our language, but they can feel love.
Text.LocalizedString: You should never be rude to your animals.//They may not understand our language, but they can feel love.

Text.SourceString: One way to give your animals love is to make sure you talk to them every day.//Petting them is a great way to show love as well.
Text.LocalizedString: One way to give your animals love is to make sure you talk to them every day.//Petting them is a great way to show love as well.

Text.SourceString: Are you doing okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Let me or <NPCName>Kenny</> know if you need anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you doing okay, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Let me or <NPCName>Kenny</> know if you need anything.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Jack</> is lost in thought.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Jack</> is lost in thought.]

Text.SourceString: Have you ever tried yoga? It’s a surprisingly good workout.//<portrait=surprised>Oh! You’re a yogi? No way!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever tried yoga? It’s a surprisingly good workout.//<portrait=surprised>Oh! You’re a yogi? No way!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kira</> got me into yoga. It helps to stretch stiff muscles.//So, tell me, are all Pokyoites into yoga, or just you?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kira</> got me into yoga. It helps to stretch stiff muscles.//So, tell me, are all Pokyoites into yoga, or just you?

Text.SourceString: I’m curious about the stories people may have told you about <NPCName>Kira</>.//My wife is a bit of a legend around here.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m curious about the stories people may have told you about <NPCName>Kira</>.//My wife is a bit of a legend around here.

Text.SourceString: She used to camp out in caverns back in the day.//<portrait=surprised>To clear out the ghouls and stuff.//<portrait=happy>I don’t know for sure. I’ve never been inside a cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: She used to camp out in caverns back in the day.//<portrait=surprised>To clear out the ghouls and stuff.//<portrait=happy>I don’t know for sure. I’ve never been inside a cavern.

Text.SourceString: I tried to cook a big dinner for the whole family last night.//<portrait=happy>If you heard <NPCName>Kenny</> shouting all the way over at your place, that was probably why.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to cook a big dinner for the whole family last night.//<portrait=happy>If you heard <NPCName>Kenny</> shouting all the way over at your place, that was probably why.

Text.SourceString: I had no idea food could blow up like that! But it’s okay.//<portrait=happy>We’re all learning, am I right?//<portrait=normal>As long as we have fun and don’t give up. That’s the key to successful cooking.
Text.LocalizedString: I had no idea food could blow up like that! But it’s okay.//<portrait=happy>We’re all learning, am I right?//<portrait=normal>As long as we have fun and don’t give up. That’s the key to successful cooking.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to walk slowly and take in all the island’s sights.//There’s no reason to go too fast.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to walk slowly and take in all the island’s sights.//There’s no reason to go too fast.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kenny’s</> a daydreamer, but he has his head on straight.//He’s a good kid.//<portrait=happy>He’s also a good flute player. Just like his mother.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kenny’s</> a daydreamer, but he has his head on straight.//He’s a good kid.//<portrait=happy>He’s also a good flute player. Just like his mother.

Text.SourceString: The ranch is closing early today, so make sure you get whatever you need soon.
Text.LocalizedString: The ranch is closing early today, so make sure you get whatever you need soon.

Text.SourceString: Do you need something from the ranch? It isn’t urgent, is it?//<portrait=normal>Oh good! Then let’s just wait until tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you need something from the ranch? It isn’t urgent, is it?//<portrait=normal>Oh good! Then let’s just wait until tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I should have done inventory last night, but I got caught up watching the cooking show.//<portrait=surprised>Wow! That show can hypnotize you for hours!
Text.LocalizedString: I should have done inventory last night, but I got caught up watching the cooking show.//<portrait=surprised>Wow! That show can hypnotize you for hours!

Text.SourceString: The vineyard? Hmm… No, I don’t really hang out there.//<portrait=concerned>Don’t know that <NPCName>Walter</> guy that well, either.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Kira</> knows his wife, though.
Text.LocalizedString: The vineyard? Hmm… No, I don’t really hang out there.//<portrait=concerned>Don’t know that <NPCName>Walter</> guy that well, either.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Kira</> knows his wife, though.

Text.SourceString: Part of running the ranch is selling items and keeping up with stock.//<NPCName>Kenny</> would rather be out with the animals, so I handle the store part.
Text.LocalizedString: Part of running the ranch is selling items and keeping up with stock.//<NPCName>Kenny</> would rather be out with the animals, so I handle the store part.

Text.SourceString: Do you prefer sweet or savory foods?//<portrait=surprised>I like them all. Kimchi, fruit tarts… <Italic>Any</> fruit tarts!
Text.LocalizedString: Do you prefer sweet or savory foods?//<portrait=surprised>I like them all. Kimchi, fruit tarts… <Italic>Any</> fruit tarts!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kira</> isn’t a picky eater. I don’t think she loves or hates any particular foods.//She sure loves flowers, though.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kira</> isn’t a picky eater. I don’t think she loves or hates any particular foods.//She sure loves flowers, though.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about getting me anything for my birthday.//<NPCName>Kira</> and I don’t celebrate birthdays.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about getting me anything for my birthday.//<NPCName>Kira</> and I don’t celebrate birthdays.

Text.SourceString: What did you do before you came to Coral Island, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What did you do before you came to Coral Island, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Corporate folk, huh? That’s chill.//<portrait=normal>You must have worked in tall buildings, huh? I’m impressed.
Text.LocalizedString: Corporate folk, huh? That’s chill.//<portrait=normal>You must have worked in tall buildings, huh? I’m impressed.

Text.SourceString: You gave him cheese, huh? That’s too bad. I hope he wasn’t rude about it.//But yeah, <NPCName>Kenny</> doesn’t eat cheese, eggs. Things like that.
Text.LocalizedString: You gave him cheese, huh? That’s too bad. I hope he wasn’t rude about it.//But yeah, <NPCName>Kenny</> doesn’t eat cheese, eggs. Things like that.

Text.SourceString: People have offered to help me take inventory at the ranch, but I always turn them down.//It feels good to do it myself.
Text.LocalizedString: People have offered to help me take inventory at the ranch, but I always turn them down.//It feels good to do it myself.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kira</> said I ought to spend more time at the Tavern making new friends.//She thinks it would be good for me.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kira</> said I ought to spend more time at the Tavern making new friends.//She thinks it would be good for me.

Text.SourceString: I’m from here, so I know a lot of these folks already.//<portrait=normal>But I don’t know them as well as my parents do.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m from here, so I know a lot of these folks already.//<portrait=normal>But I don’t know them as well as my parents do.

Text.SourceString: I’ll have to look for more animal feed to stock.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Ben</> is helpful with this type of thing.//<portrait=normal>He’s young and gathers feed quickly. Which is weird, ’cause he walks really slowly.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll have to look for more animal feed to stock.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Ben</> is helpful with this type of thing.//<portrait=normal>He’s young and gathers feed quickly. Which is weird, ’cause he walks really slowly.

Text.SourceString: Has <NPCName>Kenny</> taught you about the animals’ moods yet?//I bet he has. So, your animals will get upset if you don’t feed them.
Text.LocalizedString: Has <NPCName>Kenny</> taught you about the animals’ moods yet?//I bet he has. So, your animals will get upset if you don’t feed them.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kenny’s</> such an eager beaver, that kid.//He’s been like that since he was a tiny tot.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kenny’s</> such an eager beaver, that kid.//He’s been like that since he was a tiny tot.

Text.SourceString: Do you grow most of your own food?//I assume farmers do that.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you grow most of your own food?//I assume farmers do that.

Text.SourceString: Me, farming? No, it’s not for me.//Besides, who’s going to take care of my ranch if I farm?//<portrait=surprised>Hmm. Solid point. I do have <NPCName>Kenny</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Me, farming? No, it’s not for me.//Besides, who’s going to take care of my ranch if I farm?//<portrait=surprised>Hmm. Solid point. I do have <NPCName>Kenny</>.

Text.SourceString: It’s rough when rude customers come to the ranch.//It’s not everyone, or even most people. It’s just a few prickly individuals.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s rough when rude customers come to the ranch.//It’s not everyone, or even most people. It’s just a few prickly individuals.

Text.SourceString: Oh! That’s what I was supposed to do yesterday. I completely forgot to get groceries.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! That’s what I was supposed to do yesterday. I completely forgot to get groceries.

Text.SourceString: Sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. What did you say?
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. What did you say?

Text.SourceString: I like Spring. It’s easier to get fresh ingredients this time of year.//<portrait=surprised>Spring and Summer. And don’t forget Fall.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm. Hang on. That’s basically the whole year.
Text.LocalizedString: I like Spring. It’s easier to get fresh ingredients this time of year.//<portrait=surprised>Spring and Summer. And don’t forget Fall.//<portrait=annoyed>Hmm. Hang on. That’s basically the whole year.

Text.SourceString: I should probably restock the ranch’s feed supply.//Everyone stocks up on feed in Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I should probably restock the ranch’s feed supply.//Everyone stocks up on feed in Spring.

Text.SourceString: What are your favorite Spring veggies, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What are your favorite Spring veggies, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Cucumber fan, huh? Not bad, not bad!//<portrait=normal>I’ve always been a big fan of lettuce.
Text.LocalizedString: Cucumber fan, huh? Not bad, not bad!//<portrait=normal>I’ve always been a big fan of lettuce.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Jim’s</> son – What’s his name?//Yeah! <NPCName>Theo</>!//<portrait=surprised>I gave him some strawberries this one time, and he told me they were…crunchy.//<portrait=happy>Sure cracked me up!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Jim’s</> son – What’s his name?//Yeah! <NPCName>Theo</>!//<portrait=surprised>I gave him some strawberries this one time, and he told me they were…crunchy.//<portrait=happy>Sure cracked me up!

Text.SourceString: I’m glad <NPCName>Kira’s</> not out hunting anymore.//Not that I don’t think she could handle it. It’s the heat!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad <NPCName>Kira’s</> not out hunting anymore.//Not that I don’t think she could handle it. It’s the heat!

Text.SourceString: I try and stick to the shade on my way to work in the mornings.//<portrait=surprised>I might melt if I spend too much time in the sun.
Text.LocalizedString: I try and stick to the shade on my way to work in the mornings.//<portrait=surprised>I might melt if I spend too much time in the sun.

Text.SourceString: People need to be careful when they let their kids swim in the ocean. I’ve heard some wild legends about what lives down there.//I won’t risk it.
Text.LocalizedString: People need to be careful when they let their kids swim in the ocean. I’ve heard some wild legends about what lives down there.//I won’t risk it.

Text.SourceString: Fall means harvest season, and harvest season means good food!//I can’t decide what to cook first!
Text.LocalizedString: Fall means harvest season, and harvest season means good food!//I can’t decide what to cook first!

Text.SourceString: This crisp Fall chill makes working outside easier.
Text.LocalizedString: This crisp Fall chill makes working outside easier.

Text.SourceString: It also makes <NPCName>Kenny’s</> flute go out of tune. Someone should probably tell him that.//<portrait=happy>Me? No. Maybe you should. You two are friends, aren’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: It also makes <NPCName>Kenny’s</> flute go out of tune. Someone should probably tell him that.//<portrait=happy>Me? No. Maybe you should. You two are friends, aren’t you?

Text.SourceString: Fresh veggies are hard to come by in Winter.//I might wait until Spring to try out new recipes again.
Text.LocalizedString: Fresh veggies are hard to come by in Winter.//I might wait until Spring to try out new recipes again.

Text.SourceString: Have you stored up enough food for Winter?//It’s hard to cook if you don’t have the right ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you stored up enough food for Winter?//It’s hard to cook if you don’t have the right ingredients.

Text.SourceString: Winter’s too cold to stay late at the ranch.//I usually go right home for a warm meal.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter’s too cold to stay late at the ranch.//I usually go right home for a warm meal.

Text.SourceString: If you need a warm place to rest during your errands, come by the ranch.//I keep it nice and toasty in there.
Text.LocalizedString: If you need a warm place to rest during your errands, come by the ranch.//I keep it nice and toasty in there.

Text.SourceString: Like humans, animals don’t like getting wet.//You should keep them inside on days like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Like humans, animals don’t like getting wet.//You should keep them inside on days like this.

Text.SourceString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Kenny</>, he’s probably inside the house.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re looking for <NPCName>Kenny</>, he’s probably inside the house.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kira</> never did mind going out in the rain. Me, I’m a little different.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kira</> never did mind going out in the rain. Me, I’m a little different.

Text.SourceString: Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.

Text.SourceString: Weather forecasting is such a sham sometimes.//<portrait=concerned>They said the rain would be over by now.
Text.LocalizedString: Weather forecasting is such a sham sometimes.//<portrait=concerned>They said the rain would be over by now.

Text.SourceString: Hot meals are great on days when the weather’s bad.//What should I cook for dinner tonight?
Text.LocalizedString: Hot meals are great on days when the weather’s bad.//What should I cook for dinner tonight?

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I’m not out in that rain.//My groceries can wait. I’m not going to <NPCName>Sam</>’s in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I’m not out in that rain.//My groceries can wait. I’m not going to <NPCName>Sam</>’s in this weather.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, have you seen my coffee cup?//I swear I left it around here somewhere.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, have you seen my coffee cup?//I swear I left it around here somewhere.

Text.SourceString: It’s time to make something hot to eat! What should I cook?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s time to make something hot to eat! What should I cook?

Text.SourceString: I hope this rain is over by morning.//It gets pretty muddy around here.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this rain is over by morning.//It gets pretty muddy around here.

Text.SourceString: I’ll have to do my yoga indoors this evening. It doesn’t look like the rain’s going to let up.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll have to do my yoga indoors this evening. It doesn’t look like the rain’s going to let up.

Text.SourceString: Make sure your animals are inside, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure your animals are inside, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: I need to get out of this before I get hurt.//Being struck by lightning is no joke.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to get out of this before I get hurt.//Being struck by lightning is no joke.

Text.SourceString: Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Jack</> is in a hurry.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Jack</> is in a hurry.]

Text.SourceString: I hope nothing gets damaged in this storm.//We can’t really afford any repairs.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope nothing gets damaged in this storm.//We can’t really afford any repairs.

Text.SourceString: The storm is fine as long as there’s no blackout.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh yeah, it’s happened, let me tell you. It’ll happen again.//<portrait=concerned>Yes, it will.
Text.LocalizedString: The storm is fine as long as there’s no blackout.//<portrait=annoyed>Oh yeah, it’s happened, let me tell you. It’ll happen again.//<portrait=concerned>Yes, it will.

Text.SourceString: I hope this storm is over by morning.//It gets pretty flooded out there.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this storm is over by morning.//It gets pretty flooded out there.

Text.SourceString: I’ll have to make something hot for dinner tonight.//Have any suggestions?
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll have to make something hot for dinner tonight.//Have any suggestions?

Text.SourceString: Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s talk another time. I need to get home.

Text.SourceString: Snow’s deep today, huh?//At least it’s warm in here.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow’s deep today, huh?//At least it’s warm in here.

Text.SourceString: The town needs to get someone to shovel the snow. It’s impossible to get around.
Text.LocalizedString: The town needs to get someone to shovel the snow. It’s impossible to get around.

Text.SourceString: It feels weird to have guests, let me tell you.//<portrait=happy>In a nice way, though. Weird nice.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels weird to have guests, let me tell you.//<portrait=happy>In a nice way, though. Weird nice.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kenny</>? Hmm. He’s either out on the ranch or in his room.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kenny</>? Hmm. He’s either out on the ranch or in his room.

Text.SourceString: This old thing doesn’t look so bad, does it?//<portrait=happy>I’ve been taking good care of this building. Look around!
Text.LocalizedString: This old thing doesn’t look so bad, does it?//<portrait=happy>I’ve been taking good care of this building. Look around!

Text.SourceString: As a matter of fact, yes! I did use to live here. This was when I was a single man. Before I moved into <NPCName>Kira’s</> house.//<portrait=happy>In that happy little room right there. Neat, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: As a matter of fact, yes! I did use to live here. This was when I was a single man. Before I moved into <NPCName>Kira’s</> house.//<portrait=happy>In that happy little room right there. Neat, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s nice of you to visit. You’re welcome to stay for dinner if you want.//<portrait=normal>I’m making plenty!
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s nice of you to visit. You’re welcome to stay for dinner if you want.//<portrait=normal>I’m making plenty!

Text.SourceString: There’s always something to be done around here.//That’s part of running a business.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s always something to be done around here.//That’s part of running a business.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen my coffee cup?//I know I set it down somewhere.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen my coffee cup?//I know I set it down somewhere.

Text.SourceString: How do you organize your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>? You should tell me about it sometime.//We can trade tips.
Text.LocalizedString: How do you organize your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>? You should tell me about it sometime.//We can trade tips.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kira</> is better at this than I am.//You should find her if you need help with yoga poses.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kira</> is better at this than I am.//You should find her if you need help with yoga poses.

Text.SourceString: Breathe in… Hold it… Breathe out.
Text.LocalizedString: Breathe in… Hold it… Breathe out.

Text.SourceString: Not a big fisher myself. I know how to take care of some animals, but you lose me at fish.
Text.LocalizedString: Not a big fisher myself. I know how to take care of some animals, but you lose me at fish.

Text.SourceString: You can probably fish in that creek near the cavern.//I see <NpcName>Joko</> fishing there all the time.//Must be something in the water, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: You can probably fish in that creek near the cavern.//I see <NpcName>Joko</> fishing there all the time.//Must be something in the water, eh?

Text.SourceString: I can make a lot of dishes with the vegetables around here.//Fish and all that too. But it doesn’t always turn out good.
Text.LocalizedString: I can make a lot of dishes with the vegetables around here.//Fish and all that too. But it doesn’t always turn out good.

Text.SourceString: Cooking is a risky business.
Text.LocalizedString: Cooking is a risky business.

Text.SourceString: Many Summers ago, I tried making an egg dish and failed horribly. Yeah, that might have been my worst cooking experiment.
Text.LocalizedString: Many Summers ago, I tried making an egg dish and failed horribly. Yeah, that might have been my worst cooking experiment.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Kenny</> teases me about it <Italic>every day</>.//<portrait=normal>Well, not every day.//Ah, that funny kid.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Kenny</> teases me about it <Italic>every day</>.//<portrait=normal>Well, not every day.//Ah, that funny kid.

Text.SourceString: What do you say I walk over to the farm after work sometime? Huh?//<portrait=normal>Now that we’re best buds.
Text.LocalizedString: What do you say I walk over to the farm after work sometime? Huh?//<portrait=normal>Now that we’re best buds.

Text.SourceString: I can show you how to properly care for your animals. Great idea, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: I can show you how to properly care for your animals. Great idea, eh?

Text.SourceString: I worry about <NpcName>Kenny</> sometimes.//He can be a bit…intense.
Text.LocalizedString: I worry about <NpcName>Kenny</> sometimes.//He can be a bit…intense.

Text.SourceString: He feels very connected to the earth. And not in a good way.//I don’t know. I might be overthinking this.
Text.LocalizedString: He feels very connected to the earth. And not in a good way.//I don’t know. I might be overthinking this.

Text.SourceString: You saw <NpcName>Kenny</> where? Playing flute for the what?!
Text.LocalizedString: You saw <NpcName>Kenny</> where? Playing flute for the what?!

Text.SourceString: I should talk to that kid. Push him back into society.//If not, I’ll just give him more work. That might do it.
Text.LocalizedString: I should talk to that kid. Push him back into society.//If not, I’ll just give him more work. That might do it.

Text.SourceString: The thing with <NpcName>Kenny</> is – well, I’m at fault for loving nature and all that jazz.//<portrait=normal>Gotta say, I taught him that. But I had no idea he’d take it this far.
Text.LocalizedString: The thing with <NpcName>Kenny</> is – well, I’m at fault for loving nature and all that jazz.//<portrait=normal>Gotta say, I taught him that. But I had no idea he’d take it this far.

Text.SourceString: Serenading the flowers. I mean, come on!
Text.LocalizedString: Serenading the flowers. I mean, come on!

Text.SourceString: When <NpcName>Kira</> does it – singing to a tree – it’s cute. But why do I worry when it comes to <NpcName>Kenny</>?
Text.LocalizedString: When <NpcName>Kira</> does it – singing to a tree – it’s cute. But why do I worry when it comes to <NpcName>Kenny</>?

Text.SourceString: It’s <Italic>not</> nothing, I gotta say.//I’m worried he might end up marrying a tree or something.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s <Italic>not</> nothing, I gotta say.//I’m worried he might end up marrying a tree or something.

Text.SourceString: His mother says <NpcName>Kenny</> is a beautiful soul. Can’t argue with that.//I think the kid will be fine.
Text.LocalizedString: His mother says <NpcName>Kenny</> is a beautiful soul. Can’t argue with that.//I think the kid will be fine.

Text.SourceString: He just needs some friends.//It isn’t healthy to be off in the middle of nowhere without much human contact for too long.
Text.LocalizedString: He just needs some friends.//It isn’t healthy to be off in the middle of nowhere without much human contact for too long.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been looking at new recipes.//This weekend is going to be the one I finally nail making kimchi.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been looking at new recipes.//This weekend is going to be the one I finally nail making kimchi.

Text.SourceString: Mark my words. I will not leave the house until I have mastered kimchi.
Text.LocalizedString: Mark my words. I will not leave the house until I have mastered kimchi.

Text.SourceString: I got some fresh seafood yesterday from the shack. I’m planning to make stew with it.//<portrait=happy>Sounds good, doesn’t it? Stew on a cold day like this?
Text.LocalizedString: I got some fresh seafood yesterday from the shack. I’m planning to make stew with it.//<portrait=happy>Sounds good, doesn’t it? Stew on a cold day like this?

Text.SourceString: Do you know how to make stew?//<portrait=concerned>I can’t remember if you need coconut water or if normal water will do. Hmm.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know how to make stew?//<portrait=concerned>I can’t remember if you need coconut water or if normal water will do. Hmm.

Text.SourceString: Failed the kimchi experiment this week. I’ll try again next week.
Text.LocalizedString: Failed the kimchi experiment this week. I’ll try again next week.

Text.SourceString: It ended up tasting pretty weird. I threw the whole batch out.//Gave me a stomachache.
Text.LocalizedString: It ended up tasting pretty weird. I threw the whole batch out.//Gave me a stomachache.

Text.SourceString: I told <NpcName>Kenny</> that when I can’t do it anymore, he needs to be the one who takes care of the animals.
Text.LocalizedString: I told <NpcName>Kenny</> that when I can’t do it anymore, he needs to be the one who takes care of the animals.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I have anything to worry about.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I have anything to worry about.

Text.SourceString: I used to spend rainy days outdoors, playing with the cows.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to spend rainy days outdoors, playing with the cows.

Text.SourceString: I had this cow, Baby.//She wasn’t a baby. Her name was Baby.//<portrait=happy>We used to be best buds. Took her to a field one rainy day. Oh boy!
Text.LocalizedString: I had this cow, Baby.//She wasn’t a baby. Her name was Baby.//<portrait=happy>We used to be best buds. Took her to a field one rainy day. Oh boy!

Text.SourceString: We almost got struck by lightning!//What a memory!
Text.LocalizedString: We almost got struck by lightning!//What a memory!

Text.SourceString: Living in a forest can be lonely for town people. If you’re like <NpcName>Sam</>, I wouldn’t recommend it.
Text.LocalizedString: Living in a forest can be lonely for town people. If you’re like <NpcName>Sam</>, I wouldn’t recommend it.

Text.SourceString: But for me, it’s perfect.//I never feel lonely for a moment. My cattle keep me company.
Text.LocalizedString: But for me, it’s perfect.//I never feel lonely for a moment. My cattle keep me company.

Text.SourceString: It’d be good for me to use the kitchen here every once in a while.
Text.LocalizedString: It’d be good for me to use the kitchen here every once in a while.

Text.SourceString: Clean up the cobwebs a little.//<portrait=surprised>Don’t want the spiders to get too comfortable in here. I still have a lot of plans for this place.
Text.LocalizedString: Clean up the cobwebs a little.//<portrait=surprised>Don’t want the spiders to get too comfortable in here. I still have a lot of plans for this place.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I live in the forest. I couldn’t imagine living anywhere else.//<portrait=happy>It’s not too noisy here, let me tell you.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I live in the forest. I couldn’t imagine living anywhere else.//<portrait=happy>It’s not too noisy here, let me tell you.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to deal with the hustle and bustle of town every day.//<portrait=surprised>I don’t think I could stand it.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to deal with the hustle and bustle of town every day.//<portrait=surprised>I don’t think I could stand it.

Text.SourceString: Last night’s episode of the cooking show was fantastic.//<portrait=normal>I think one of these days, I’m going to re-create the fruit tarts they made.
Text.LocalizedString: Last night’s episode of the cooking show was fantastic.//<portrait=normal>I think one of these days, I’m going to re-create the fruit tarts they made.

Text.SourceString: You should come to yoga with me sometime, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I think you’d enjoy it.
Text.LocalizedString: You should come to yoga with me sometime, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I think you’d enjoy it.

Text.SourceString: Besides, I saw you talking to the instructor that time. You two seemed comfortable.//<portrait=happy>Are you two…?//<portrait=normal>Never mind.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, I saw you talking to the instructor that time. You two seemed comfortable.//<portrait=happy>Are you two…?//<portrait=normal>Never mind.

Text.SourceString: I’ve lived here my entire life. So did my parents and their parents as well.//Let me say this now, before I forget.//<portrait=happy>I’m glad you moved in, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve lived here my entire life. So did my parents and their parents as well.//Let me say this now, before I forget.//<portrait=happy>I’m glad you moved in, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Someday, <NPCName>Kira</> and I might be…somewhere else. Far from here.//<portrait=happy>And I’m glad this island has someone like you to take care of it.//<portrait=normal>You’ve done plenty for Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: Someday, <NPCName>Kira</> and I might be…somewhere else. Far from here.//<portrait=happy>And I’m glad this island has someone like you to take care of it.//<portrait=normal>You’ve done plenty for Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: I need to get better about experimenting in the kitchen.//If I don’t start improving, I might not win any cooking contests. Ever.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to get better about experimenting in the kitchen.//If I don’t start improving, I might not win any cooking contests. Ever.

Text.SourceString: On the worst days, it feels like everything is leaving me behind. Nature, my youth, the entire world.//One day, I’ll just be a forgotten guy in the woods.
Text.LocalizedString: On the worst days, it feels like everything is leaving me behind. Nature, my youth, the entire world.//One day, I’ll just be a forgotten guy in the woods.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… It is what it is.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… It is what it is.

Text.SourceString: People keep telling me to sell the ranch to a big company so <NPCName>Kira</> and I can truly retire.//<portrait=annoyed>Why would I do that? This ranch has been in my family for generations, and it’ll stay that way.
Text.LocalizedString: People keep telling me to sell the ranch to a big company so <NPCName>Kira</> and I can truly retire.//<portrait=annoyed>Why would I do that? This ranch has been in my family for generations, and it’ll stay that way.

Text.SourceString: Where am I going to go, anyway? I love it here.
Text.LocalizedString: Where am I going to go, anyway? I love it here.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s nice of you to visit. You’re welcome to stay for dinner if you want.//<portrait=normal>I’m making plenty!
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s nice of you to visit. You’re welcome to stay for dinner if you want.//<portrait=normal>I’m making plenty!

Text.SourceString: Have you ever thought about starting a business? It’s not easy.//Farmers are their own businesses. You understand what I mean by that, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever thought about starting a business? It’s not easy.//Farmers are their own businesses. You understand what I mean by that, right?

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, when business is slow, I close early and tend my vegetables.//You can’t beat the flavor of the fresh stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, when business is slow, I close early and tend my vegetables.//You can’t beat the flavor of the fresh stuff.

Text.SourceString: Yoga last week was brutal.//Plenty of tough poses.//<portrait=happy>Lucky I didn’t pull anything!
Text.LocalizedString: Yoga last week was brutal.//Plenty of tough poses.//<portrait=happy>Lucky I didn’t pull anything!

Text.SourceString: Nothing is better than watching the sun rise over the trees on a Saturday morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing is better than watching the sun rise over the trees on a Saturday morning.

Text.SourceString: When I do yoga, I don’t have to think about anything else. I can just focus on the way my body feels.
Text.LocalizedString: When I do yoga, I don’t have to think about anything else. I can just focus on the way my body feels.

Text.SourceString: It’s…freeing, actually.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s…freeing, actually.

Text.SourceString: There’s this great hot sauce that goes with just about anything. XYZ brand. It kicks, all right!//<portrait=happy>I always have it in my kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s this great hot sauce that goes with just about anything. XYZ brand. It kicks, all right!//<portrait=happy>I always have it in my kitchen.

Text.SourceString: I might go in the back and lie down for a bit.//<portrait=concerned>I woke up too early today.
Text.LocalizedString: I might go in the back and lie down for a bit.//<portrait=concerned>I woke up too early today.

Text.SourceString: I brought my own tea this morning.//<portrait=annoyed>No way I’m spending – how much does a cup of tea cost these days? Thirty, fifty coins?
Text.LocalizedString: I brought my own tea this morning.//<portrait=annoyed>No way I’m spending – how much does a cup of tea cost these days? Thirty, fifty coins?

Text.SourceString: Yoga might look easy, but let me just say… It makes you sweat like you never sweat before.//I don’t know how <NpcName>Leah</> does it.
Text.LocalizedString: Yoga might look easy, but let me just say… It makes you sweat like you never sweat before.//I don’t know how <NpcName>Leah</> does it.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna spend the day here.//<portrait=happy>It would be a waste of good weather if I didn’t.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna spend the day here.//<portrait=happy>It would be a waste of good weather if I didn’t.
